This paper deals with routing algorithms and graph theory, which are both topics that fall under computer science. The paper specifically focuses on the Theta-4-graph, which is a type of geometric graph. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). However, since the paper also involves computational geometry, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is also a likely sub-category. Additionally, since the paper discusses routing algorithms, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are also possible sub-categories. Finally, since the paper involves information theory and the concept of routing ratio, cs.IT (Information Theory) is also a possible sub-category.
